{"/service/ndnp/az/batch_az_iotite_ver01/data/sn84020064/0054286641A/1930041301/0016.xml":{"full_text":"EIGHT\nPhiladelphia Han domes to Knlisf\nIn Apache Expedition and Becomes\nEnthusiastic Booster for l)ou\u00bblas\nr*\ni\nw xvin* traveled all the way from\nPhiladelphia In his Chrysler car.\nCharles H. Newhaus is in Douglas\nas a volunteer to the Fimbres\nApache expedition which was to\nhave started Into the Sierra Madre\nmountains of Sonora on May 7 but\nwhich has been denied crossing\nprivileges by the Mexican govern\nment, believed here to have been\nthe result of a request from the U. S.\nstate department at Washington.\nMr Newhaus had left his home in\nPhiladelphia before the announce\nment went out over the Associated\nPress and the United Press telling\nof the abandonment of the plans\nfor the expedition.\nMr. Newhaus traveled from his\nhome south through Baltimore and\nWashington and then across Vir\nginia and Tennessee and from\nWemphis. when he had crossed the\nMississippi river, he followed U. S.\nhighway 80 into the city of Douglas.\nHe says he found the roads good\nall the way and paved most of the\nway and that he found the rural\nportions of the country looking fine.\n\"Travel Is being made more pleas\nant and easier every fear because\nthe people are insisting on good\nroad conditions the year round,\"\nraid Mr. Newhaus. \"There is almost\nno occasion to pay toll In the south\nas there was In the old days. I\nthink that two dollars was the total\ntoll fare for me and the same route\na few years a?o would have meant\ntolls of from 810 to S2O. Saying it\nin no sense of boasting. I know\nsomething of road conditions and\ndevelopments for I have traveled\nacross this continent more than a\ndozen times, at one time having\nbeen a motor enthusiast in making\nthe test tours with same of the best\nmakes of the big cars. So I know\nthe roads and am happy to say that\nI see much Improvement In them.\nWe are living in a great age.\"\nWhen Mr. Newhaus learned of the\naction of the Mexican government\nIn denying the expedition crossing\nrights, he smiled, looked about and\nremarked: \u2022Well, It appears that\nI\u2019ve come to a pretty good country\nall right and I'm going to make a\nvisit anyhow, I've been In Arizona\nbefore and know it is a fine place\nand It might happen that coming\nto go on this expedition would re\nsult in my joining the ranks of Ari\nzona residents for I am seriously\ninclined to wire my wife to ship the\nfurniture and come west.\u201d\nThat the Fimbres Apache publi\ncity got attention through the east\nis emphasized by Mr. Newhaus. whoj\ndeclares that the stories about it\ncaused Quite general interest among\nreaders throughout the east. \"And\nlet me tell you this,\" said he, dis\ncussing the matter. \u201cJust forget\nthe Indiana in the picture\u2014in fact\nI think that possibly is the cause\nof the action of the Mexican gov-\neminent concerning the expedition\n\u201cTake the Indians out of the pic\nture and you still have one of the\ngreatest attractions on the globe\nand certainly the most interesting\non this continent right here on the\nborder near Douglas.\n\u201cThere is a hunting and fishing\narea that has no superior anywhere\nand I think it has no equal. De\nvelop it. Get the facts to the peo\nple who seek recreation in the great\noutdoors. Have pictures made of,\nthe cliff dwellers\u2019 former abode.\nOet pictures of the wild life \u2014deer,\nbears, turkey, pheasants, the gaily\ncolored birds, the forest growth and\nsend them to the people in the\nnorth and east. Make Douglas the\nheadquarters of a great sports area\nwhere hunting or fishing may be\nenjoyed every day in the year. Then\nstir further interest in exploration\nof those interesting areas where it\nis claimed the old Spanish explorers\nfound native gold and silver and\nyou will have your splendid hotel\ncrowded every week of the year and\nwill need more hotels. The people\nwho have money want that sort of\na setting for their playground. You\n.have it. Get busy *and sell it to\nthem.\n\u201cYou have an airfield here that\nRe-roof the \"GenascoWay\u201d\nFront View of a Geiutro\nLaute Shingle. In tlu*\u00ab\nnatural, ua/achaa color*\u2014\nred, cad blue black.\nBark View of a Oraaaro\nLatitr Shingle ahoanng the\n\u201ckey\" that lock* each\nakiagle tigbtly to thoaa\n(jQn&SCQ Shingles\nm \u00ab_\nChamp Debaters\n;I Ml\n\nThree of the nation\u2019s champion\ncollege debaters, crowned In a re\ncent contest at Wichita, Kan., are\npictured here. Above Is Evelyn\nHunter of Southwestern College,\nWlnfleld, Kan., a member of the\nwinning team of women; below,\nVery! Pitts, University of Wichita,\nIndividual men\u2019s champion, and\nWanda Morton, West Virginia\nWesleyan, Individual womeu\u2019a\nchampion.\nIs remarkably good. They will be\ni coming here by plane for the sort\nof sport-you can sell them. Auto\nmobiles are too slow for that tribe\nof sportsmen. What does that sort\nof a man care for a few dollars?\nHe\u2019s looking for entertainment\u2014\nthrills. Thrills are his entertain\nment and you can't get them flying\nover wheat fields or corn fields.\nThey come from scaling dangerous\nmountain peaks trudging through\nthe canyons to stalk game, riding\nover the mesa in the hope of find\ning some game as target for your\nmarksmanship. That\u2019s what you\nhave. Sell it to them.\n\u201cIt will Interest you. I am sure,\nto know that there is all along the\nway east on U. 8. highway 80 a\ngeneral and enthusiastic under\nstanding to let the world know that\nthis is the only \u2018all-year-all\nweather\u2019 cross-continent route.\nThere will soon be the road work\nthrough Arkansas that will handle\nthe situation during the rainy sea\nson that has meant floods. With\nthat completed, it will be possible\nfor millionaires in New York and all\nthe big cities in the east to come\nhere by automobile any month in\nthe year 11 they want the automo\nbile trip. Otherwise they can fly.\nGet the stage set for them. Develop\nyour hunting ground.\n\u201cSince arriving, 1 have taken the\ntime to call upon Mr. Emiliano\nTamez, the Mexican consul here,\nand after a talk with Consul Tamez.\nI am sure that the Mexican gov\nernment will favor developing a\nhunting ground In the Sierras. Con\nsul Tamez showed the keenest Inter\nest in the idea and assured me that\nhis government wants to grant priv\nilege to all Americans who would\nlike to make such a trip and that\nthe charges for such passports are\nonly nominal. So it is my belief\nthat if you will turn the effort to\nattracting attention to this great\narea of opportunity for sportsmen,\nthe Flmbres Apache expedition ad\nvertising will not have gone in vain\nand incidentally, it wllL not be as\nHard on the skin of the Apaches\nas a genuine expedition to drive\nthem out might have meant.\u201d\n-and pay in 10 months\nYou con buy a new Oenasco Lethe Shingle\nroof, or any Gcnaaco roofing, just as conven\niently as you nrcy have bought your hon.e or\nmotor car\u2014in easy monthly installments, out\nof your current income.\nGenasco Latite Shingles are etpcc ially adapt*\ned for laying right over your old wood shingles.\nYou save time, trouble and money in the\nbargain by re-roofing the \u201cGcrmaco Way\".\nCome in and let us give you more details.\nDOUGLAS PLANING\nMILL\nG 24-640 13th St Phone 312\nDOUGLAS DAILY DISPATCH. SUNDAY MORNING. APRIL 13, 1930.\nChevrolet Sales\nOf Used Cars Are\nMaking a Record\nDETROIT. April 12 An indica\ntion of the rapid exi>ansion of the\nused car market and an assurance\nof a brightened business outlook was\nrevealed tn an announcement by\n{the Chevrolet Motor company today\nthat winter sales of used cars by\nthe nation-wide Chevrolet dealer oi\nganlzatlon are exceeding by more\nthan 25 per cent the best previous\nwinter record.\nDespite the extremely cold and\nstormy weather in the northern\nstates In January and adverse\nweather conditions in some other\nsections, sales of used cars by Ch\u00ab\nrolet dealers during thr month to\ntaled 60.000 cars as compared with\nthe January record of 48.000 \\stab\nlished last year.\nA quickening of general business\nI and unusually mild weather In Feb\nruary assured a new record for that\nmonth even though final figures for\nthe last ten days of the month arc\nnot yet available. Reports fron.\ndealers for the first 20 days of Feb\nruary show an Increase of 54 4 per\ncent over the corresponding period\nof February last year. During the\nfirst 20 days of February. 1930 tin-\nChevrolet dealer organization sold\n.58.922 used cars, nearly equalling in\n2b days the record month of Janu\nary. The stature of the February\nachievement may be further appre\nciated by a comparison of this fig\nure with 38.176 used cars sold dur\ning the corresponding period of\nFebruary last year\nJewish Services\nSpring Festival\nOf the Fassover\nJews of Douglas started the ob\nservance of the Passover last eve\nning but the ilrst of the services\nceleb: ating the Passover will be held\nthis morning at 8. Nathan Cohen\nis president of the local congrega\ntion. The services will be conduct\ned in Irene hall. The local organi\nzation Is known as Congregation\nAdath Israel.\nPassover was first a spring festi\nval in Palestine. It marked the\nreaping of the barley harvest. The\nfirst fruits of the harvest were of\nfered at the Temple of Jerusalem.\nLater. Passover came to be the an\nniversary of the liberation of the\nIsraelites from Egyptian bondage\nTo the present generation of Jews\nit ir>cans liberation from both phy\nsical oppression and hatred and from\nspiritual bondage\nEight days are set aside for the\ncelebration, during which no leav\nened bread may be eaten.\nALPINE PLANES MAY USE SKIS\nPESCOCQSTANZO, Italy,, OP)\nMinister of Aeronautics General\nBalbo hUrielf has carried out ex\nperiments here with a touring plane\nfurnished with ski-landing-gear in\nstead of wheels. Balbo took off and\nlanded on the snow both on a reg\nular landing field and on chance\nfields chosen from the air. His ex\nperiments may bring a great change\nin trans-Alpine flying, and may.\nlead to the equipping of all Italian\nplanes in this region with skis.\n\nDispatch Telephones--* 1-82. j|\nA, f\nas money can build\nor buy\nIt is natural to want the best. Public\npreference invariably follows the\narrival of a superior product.\nAnd there is a best. Always, there\nis some manufacturer unwilling to\nbe satisfied with an average result.\nIn motor cars, one manufacturer\nwho insists upon a superior prod\nuct is Nash.\nNo manufacturer has finer facil\nities to produce fine cars than Nash.\nNone lays down any more rigid\nstandards for materials and crafts\nmanship.\nThe Twin-Ignition Eight, the Twin-\nSINGLE SIX TWIN-IGNITION SIX TWIN-IGNITION EIGHT\n$935 to $1155 $1325 to $1745 $1675 to $2385\nAll prices o. b. factory \u2014Com-enienl Monthly Payment Plan if Desired\nNASH 400'\nI\nDouglas Nash Company\n910 F Avenue Telephone 294\nRobinson\u2019s Foe\nTurn W. Jinpli.ll, a!,...... Little\ni Rock. Ark., lawyer. Is a candidate\nfor the post now held by United\nf States Senator Joseph T. Robin\nson, 1928 Democratic vice presi\ndential nominee. This Is the sec\nond time Robinson has been op\nposed in a Democratic primary\nelate 1912 when he wus elected\ngovernor.\n\nALLEN IN AUTO CLASSIC\nINDIANAPOLIS \u2022A\u2019.\u2014Leslie Allen,\nPasadena, will enter th? big league\nof auto ruring for the first time\nin the international classic here in\nMay. A sparkling car. with chrom\nium plated chassis and wheels, is\nbeing built as his mount.\nHfCi GROWTH IN\nBRITISH RI'RHKK\nWASHINGTON rub\nber industry is registering consid\nerable expansion. Statistics Just re\nleased show that deliveries of crude\nrubber to manufacturers last year\nalmost doubled the amount of 1928.\n11\n\u201cNo Breakfast Complete Without\nThe Dispatch**\nj No Drip No Drip\nA Delicious Frozen Confection\nd \u2014Better Than Ever\u2014\nASSORTED FLAVORS TODAY\n0 LEMON\u2014VANILLA\nQ LIME\u2014ORANGE\nSTRAWBERRY\u2014CHERRY R\nB CHOCOLATE R\nALASKA SUCKERS CO. j\nOF DOUGLAS\n'a Sll G Avenue 0\nIgnition Six, and the Single Six\nrepresent three cars in three pop\nular price fields as fine as money\ncan build or buy.\nN ash Features\nYou Should Know\nCentralized chassis lubrication, built-in,\nautomatic radiator shutters, and the world\u2019s\neasiest steering in every model. Adjustable\nfront seats. Steel spring covers with lifts\ntime lubrication, in the Twin-Ignition\nEight and Twin-Ignition Six lines. The\npriceless protection at no extra cost of\nDuplate, non-shalterable plate gla;s in all\ndoors, windows, and windshields thruout\nthe Twin-Ignition Eight line. This glass is\nalso available at slight extra cost in all\nother Nash cars.\nWater Leakage\n\na uses Trouble\nWith liable Fine\nNcr licence in Closing\nFire Hydrant Is Blamed\nfor Wire Shorting.\nWhen a fire pltig is not prop\nerly turned off and Is permitted\nto give out a small stream of\nwater nothing disastrous results\nuhka that Hr.- plug is triUiin the\narea where the \"white way\u201d light\ncables run under the streets. On!\nMonday a leak In a fire plug was\nrepotted to the city water depart-!\nmenl.\nAt about the same tune a leak\nin the electric cables was reported.\nto the Arizona Edison com pan.,.!\nWater department employes seek\ning the leaky fire hydrant ran inttj\na crew from the F.dtson company\nseeking the leaky cable. It deVel-1\noped that tile leaky lire plug, situ-\nat?d at Seventh street and G ave\nnue. had let water seep under the\npavement and Into the cable.\nWorkers from the water depart\nment blunted the leaky plug on\ncity employes using It to secure\nwater and railing to turn it off\nproperly. The Edison company\nilnenien spent many weary hours\ndigging and prying about to get\nup their water-logged, shorted cable\nand repair it. The damage was\nvariomly estimated at from SIOO\nto 9300 It Is said that a rule\nwill be made that city employes\nshall not tamper with fire plugs\nwithin the area where the big\n\"white way\u201d cables run under the\nitreets.\n\nNearly 20.C90.000 gallons of gaso-\nline were consumed in Florida dur\ning February.\nTHERE\u2019S A\nTREND TO\nVALUE\nAMERICA IS CHOOSING\nBUICK\nACCEPT THIS\nINVITATION-\nProve BUICK supremacy in traffic, on hills, on\nthe straightaway\u2014choose the car that\u2019s win\nning two-to-one buyer preference in its field.\nMay we make just one suggestion:\nTake the wheel of a BUICK and ex\nperience the full measure of its\nabilities before buying any car.\nThen buy according to resultsl\nPerformance! That's what you want\n...performance plus the exceptional\nbeauty of Body by Fisher... and a\nride In any one of the 15 Buick\nmodels will prove a revelation of\nBUICK MOTOR COMPANY, FLINT. MICHIGAN\nCanadian Factories Division of General Motors Sailders of\nMcloughlin Buick. Oshowa, On*. Corporation ahd .Marquette Motor Cm\nSouthern Arizona Auto Co.\nDouglas GEO. E. JACKSON Lowell\nWHi. BETTER AUTOMOBILES ABE BUILT. SUIC* WILL BUILD THEM\nSmashing Proof\n...of greatest value\nAs established in Continent-wide\ntests, by 5,000 New Essex Challengers\nAll motordom saw the amazing results of Challenger\nWeek.\nThe New Essex Challenger set outstanding marks in\nevery locality. It climbed hills seldom attempted by any\ncar. It set new marks for acceleration. It established\neconomy results never before associated with such per\nformance. It made inter-city reliability and endurance\nruns that take place with the industry\u2019s great marks.\nThe really important thing is that equally\ntine marks were made by Essex right here\nin this locality. And you will find the same\ntrue no matter what city or community you\nvisit. Forthese feats were established\u2014not\nby just a few hand-picked specially tuned\ncars\u2014but 5,000 Essex Challengers in all\nparts of the country, many of them owner\ndriven. The results speak for what any\nand ever)\u2019 New Essex Challenger can do.\nYou will be delighted with Essex beauty.\nInteriors are luxuriously finished. 'There\nare eight models and a wide choice of\ncolors at no extra cost. 'The New Essex\nChallenger has victoriously proved the\nmost satisfactory quality car of low cost\nthat the market affords.\nMotor Transit Company\nDouglas Bisbee\nDispateh Telephone 81-82\npower, flexibility, swiftness, smooth\nness and stamina.\nFine car owners everywhere are pre\nferring Buick. In fact, so marked is the\ntrend to Buick that America is award\ning it from 35 to 50 per cent of the\ncombined sales of the fifteen makes\nin its price class. But be your own\njudge of Buick's performance and\nvalue. Come, take th* wheel I\nWe continue our invitation to Ride\u2014Ride\nRide! Know\u2019 from personal experience\nwhat this brilliant New Essex Challenger\ncan do. Then no lesser car can satisfy.\nf t 1\nsfmm mat COUPE-(t vithrvm-\nJ X W ble 5750)\n\u2018l7l Coach 5765\nStandard Sedan\nS B2s\u2014 Touring Sedan 5575\u2014 Brougham\n5595 Sunsedan S99s\u2014Essex Com\nmercial Chassis 5445.\nPrices f. o. b. Detroit. Factory\nIncluded in Standard Equipment: Four\nt wo- way shock absorbers\u2014Starter on dash\nRadiator shutters\u2014Electrolock Elec\ntric fuel and oil gauge on dash.\nA WIDE CHOICE OF COLORS AT NO\nEXTRA COST.\nDOUGLAS, ARIZONA.","height":"26205","width":"20301"}}
